{"questionId":"30439028","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABC</mtext></math> of a circle with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>. The angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext><mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>A&nbsp;circle with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math> and radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> is inscribed in sector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABC</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AC</mtext></math> are both tangent to the circle at points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math> respectively.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/6258d0c4397dd18a23e8c0cccf8d5fb759ef34d7.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext></math> represents the shaded region shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/288b67441762104e4e32dfa0bb3b5637f82290c5.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math> for which the area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext></math> is equal to the area of the circle of&nbsp;centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math> and radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equating their area formula to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>correct equation in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math></p>\n<p>valid approach to solve the equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>218979</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>219</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30439028","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.8c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of α for which the area of R is equal to the area of the circle of centre O and radius r.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}